    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but isn't the 'failure' part mostly just because people focus on the democracy side of things? if you look at it from a realism standpoint—like, did it successfully remove a hostile dictator and prevent a regional spillover during a critical time—wasn't it actually a win for Western interests even if the local politics went sideways?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
